title: 304 Not Modified
summary:
The HTTP 304 Not Modified client redirection response code indicates that there is no need to retransmit the requested resources.
  This response code is sent when the request is a conditional GET or HEAD request with an If-None-Match or an If-Modified-Since header and the condition evaluates to false.
  It is an implicit redirection to a cached resource that would have resulted in a 200 OK response if the condition evaluated to true.
